First, you need to make a map to get your dispatch actions. You can do this by creating a function/arrow function that returns the props, like this (if you&#39;re using a function to perform the action, make sure to IMPORT the function as well):

    const mapDispatchToProps = (dispatch) =&gt; {
     return {
     someAction: () =&gt; dispatch(actionFunction())
    }
    }

You can also dispatch directly the type of action:

    const mapDispatchToProps = (dispatch) =&gt; {
     return {
     someAction: () =&gt; dispatch({type: &quot;ACTION_TYPE&quot;})
    }
    }

and then connect it to the function:

    export default connect ({}, mapDispatchToProps) (yourComponent);

You can see more in the doc below:
https://react-redux.js.org/using-react-redux/connect-mapdispatch

